==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homograph
<hw>Hom"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"omo`grafos</grk> with the same letters; <grk>"omo`s</grk> the same
+ <grk>gra`fein</grk> to write.]</ety> <fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>One of
two or more words identical in orthography, but having different
derivations and meanings; <as>as, <ex>fair</ex>, <pos>n.</pos>, a
market, and <ex>fair</ex>, <pos>a.</pos>, beautiful</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homographic</ent>⟦br⟧
